- [IP Assignment - Potential Collaborator](/IP Assignment - potential collaborator.pdf) Used for projects **before** incorporation to assign IP to a single person ("kingmaker") who is trusted.  This is ideal for FYDP and other projects where one wants to continue on with the project.

- [IP License and Joint Venture Agreement](/IP License and Joint Venture Agreement.doc) Used for projects **before** incorporation to provide a license to each team member to the necessary IP.  Should be used only if the potential collaborator document is deemed unacceptable.

- [IP Assignment - Founder Post Incorporation](/IP Assignment - Founder Post Incorporation) Used **after** incorporation for a new founder to assign IP into the company.

- [IP Assignment - Founder on Incorporation](/IP Assignment Founder on incorporation.pdf) Used **during** incorporation for the founders to assign IP into the company.


